Subject: [PATCH 12/12] Register ISASync / CheckpointPerISC / ToolFailureTracker hooks

Upstream issue: danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1134

Three hook files ship with v5.0.0 but are not registered in
settings.json, so they never fire:

  hooks/ISASync.hook.ts
    PostToolUse(Write/Edit on ISA.md) — sync ISA frontmatter phase
    to MEMORY/STATE/work.json + kitty tab title.

  hooks/CheckpointPerISC.hook.ts
    PostToolUse(Write/Edit on ISA.md) — auto-commit checkpoint repo
    on every [ ]→[x] ISC transition.

  hooks/ToolFailureTracker.hook.ts
    PostToolUseFailure — append structured failure events to
    MEMORY/OBSERVABILITY/tool-failures.jsonl.

All three are referenced as live subsystems in:
  PAI/ALGORITHM/v6.3.0.md (phase tracking, checkpoints)
  PAI/DOCUMENTATION/ARCHITECTURE_SUMMARY.md Pipeline Topology

But they are silent — phase changes don't reach work.json, no per-ISC
checkpoint commits, no tool-failure observability.

Fix: extend settings.json's hooks block:

  - Add 1 entry to PostToolUse with matcher "Edit|Write" containing
    both ISASync.hook.ts and CheckpointPerISC.hook.ts. async: true
    so they don't block the Edit/Write call.
  - Add new PostToolUseFailure top-level event with one entry
    pointing to ToolFailureTracker.hook.ts. async: true, timeout 5.

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/settings.json                              :235

Total: 1 file, 1 hunk, +29 lines added (2 new array entries +
1 new top-level event key).

Co-existence: no prior patch (0001-0011) modifies settings.json.
JSON validity verified post-patch via jq:
  .hooks.PostToolUse | length == 8 (was 7; added 1)
  .hooks.PostToolUseFailure | length == 1 (was missing; added)
  .hooks.PostToolUse[7].matcher == "Edit|Write"
  .hooks.PostToolUse[7].hooks[0,1].command point to ISASync,
    CheckpointPerISC respectively.
  .hooks.PostToolUseFailure[0].hooks[0].command points to
    ToolFailureTracker.

Hunks generated via diff -u against the upstream tarball
(/nix/store/zm296ivyw3qg1a2fm4aa7ns10f3ldy4c-v5.0.0.tar.gz). No
hand-counted @@ headers.
